  {
    "client_msg_id": "56d7665d-7f83-477b-ae74-8da88f27fe2d",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "It all depends on intention, and it's worth being very conscious of one's intentions and drawing a hard line in one's mind between a configuration format and a DSL. The world is awash in configuration formats that slowly accumulated features and backed into Turing-completeness. A classic example is Apache configuration. Google Analytics is another one. YAML might also qualify, though I don't recall if they intended to make it Turing-complete from the start.\n\nThat's one advantage of embedding in a real language: no illusions. You can't slide down a slippery slope if you start at the bottom.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "ts": "1631030080.120900",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
